{
  "stem": "10353.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Now, to backtrack, prior to getting to Bergen-Belsen, the freight car doors opened up and the orders came from the SS, anybody that has any watches, gold pieces should surrender it or else they will be shot on site.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "So that was the first confiscation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "When we arrived in Bergen-Belsen, we were marched to this tent.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And you had a little knapsack.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "You had some things in your pocket, whatever, had to-- you had to surrender before you got-- first you got a beating and then you had to surrender all those things and march through empty-handed.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And then we were marched into a barrack.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And we were given a wooden bunk, bunk bed, three tiers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And that I remember, it sort of sunk in for the first time that what-- what really took place, what happened.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] It was like coming out from a dream and I remember breaking out in tears.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[DRINKS] Being away such huge distance from your home town, not knowing what happened to your parents, what happened to your sisters.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And here you are just nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The following day, we were told to line up and to go to the showers, to leave the clothes on one side and you come out on the other side.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The rumor was that we are going to get some special clothes on the other side.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "We took the shower, no soap or anything of the sort.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember by the time we came out on the other side, we were told no, no, to go back and to take back our own clothes.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So we took back our own clothes and we went back to the barracks again.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
